1
00:00:00,276 --> 00:00:00,850
(Previously)
Maey!

2
00:00:01,070 --> 00:00:02,516
Last night

3
00:00:02,849 --> 00:00:05,080
I saw creeping in the big house.

4
00:00:05,298 --> 00:00:06,363
What are you doing?

5
00:00:06,529 --> 00:00:07,410
This is downstairs!

6
00:00:07,446 --> 00:00:08,660
Someone might see us.

7
00:00:08,702 --> 00:00:09,690
No one will see us.

8
00:00:09,792 --> 00:00:10,361
Ahem.

9
00:00:11,454 --> 00:00:13,040
Are you trying to tell me something?

10
00:00:13,419 --> 00:00:16,770
After this, if you must be strict,

11
00:00:16,955 --> 00:00:17,646
then do so.

12
00:00:17,932 --> 00:00:18,826
Because otherwise,

13
00:00:18,849 --> 00:00:20,380
it's the people under your control

14
00:00:20,522 --> 00:00:23,060
that will ruin the honor you've earned.

15
00:00:23,520 --> 00:00:24,926
Can I ask something from you?

16
00:00:25,235 --> 00:00:25,800
What is it?

17
00:00:26,750 --> 00:00:29,310
Could you be my dance partner?

18
00:00:53,930 --> 00:00:54,760
It's raining like this.

19
00:00:55,175 --> 00:00:56,905
How is the party going?

20
00:00:59,325 --> 00:01:00,330
Forget it, Jom.

21
00:01:02,005 --> 00:01:05,505
Now there's only two of us in this house.

22
00:01:08,930 --> 00:01:09,240
Ugh!

23
00:01:14,515 --> 00:01:15,680
You're soaking wet, Khun Yai.

24
00:01:17,205 --> 00:01:20,480
Why don't you let me undress you?

25
00:01:20,915 --> 00:01:21,555
So you won't catch a cold.

26
00:01:23,885 --> 00:01:24,285
There you go.

27
00:02:37,850 --> 00:02:38,930
Let me do the same for you,

28
00:02:45,810 --> 00:02:46,695
or you'll have a fever.

29
00:04:36,495 --> 00:04:37,560
I love you, Jom.

30
00:04:41,110 --> 00:04:42,480
I love you too, Khun Yai.

31
00:06:12,600 --> 00:06:16,600
(I Feel You Linger in the Air)
(Episode 8)

32
00:06:41,350 --> 00:06:42,610
Are you awake, Khun Yai?

33
00:06:43,441 --> 00:06:47,416
So I'll put away your stuff there.

34
00:06:49,120 --> 00:06:53,490
Jom, the sun hasn't yet risen.

35
00:06:55,485 --> 00:06:56,250
Why don't you stay here a little longer?

36
00:08:01,460 --> 00:08:02,330
Jom?

37
00:08:06,180 --> 00:08:07,160
Do you see something?

38
00:08:10,120 --> 00:08:10,855
No, I don't, Khun Yai.

39
00:08:12,375 --> 00:08:12,970
It's nothing.

40
00:08:49,320 --> 00:08:50,465
No matter what,

41
00:08:53,570 --> 00:08:55,530
I will always be with you right here.

42
00:09:28,050 --> 00:09:28,600
Khun Eeang Peung.

43
00:09:29,930 --> 00:09:30,730
Khun Eeang Peung.

44
00:09:37,360 --> 00:09:38,010
Maey.

45
00:09:39,600 --> 00:09:40,760
I had a nightmare.

46
00:09:46,020 --> 00:09:46,860
Oh! It will be all right.

47
00:09:47,690 --> 00:09:48,460
It's all right.

48
00:09:48,475 --> 00:09:49,595
It's nothing.

49
00:09:50,805 --> 00:09:52,330
It was such a bad dream.

50
00:09:55,535 --> 00:09:56,975
What was it like?

51
00:10:05,700 --> 00:10:09,020
Please make yourself at home.

52
00:10:14,090 --> 00:10:15,760
These vegetables and fruit,

53
00:10:15,940 --> 00:10:17,200
you cut them all yourself?

54
00:10:18,210 --> 00:10:19,080
No, I didn't.

55
00:10:19,920 --> 00:10:22,215
These cut vegetables and fruit,

56
00:10:22,561 --> 00:10:24,826
my daughter Eeang Peung did it all.

57
00:10:30,626 --> 00:10:31,716
How exquisite!

58
00:10:46,390 --> 00:10:48,830
Ah, eat up.

59
00:10:50,705 --> 00:10:51,910
How do you find Robert

60
00:10:52,405 --> 00:10:53,690
after having conversed with him?

61
00:10:55,335 --> 00:10:57,260
He's like what you've said.

62
00:10:57,535 --> 00:10:59,560
Hmh... He looks quite accomplished.

63
00:11:00,120 --> 00:11:01,910
He is humble

64
00:11:02,590 --> 00:11:04,650
and strong at the same time.

65
00:11:05,025 --> 00:11:06,750
Yeah, right.

66
00:11:08,365 --> 00:11:12,445
He has climbed up to become
a forest owner at such an age.

67
00:11:13,445 --> 00:11:16,810
Not to mention his power
in business negotiation.

68
00:11:17,630 --> 00:11:19,940
He's quite ambitious, isn't he?

69
00:11:21,205 --> 00:11:22,650
By the way,

70
00:11:23,315 --> 00:11:25,650
Robert, as a middleman,
could be of help to you,

71
00:11:26,285 --> 00:11:27,820
who have just moved here,

72
00:11:28,410 --> 00:11:32,740
in strengthening your power in
official and commercial affairs.

73
00:11:33,235 --> 00:11:33,725
I think...

74
00:11:38,880 --> 00:11:43,550
Mother, I overheard Father
and Uncle Dech talking.

75
00:11:44,440 --> 00:11:48,295
It seems like they want me

76
00:11:50,215 --> 00:11:52,670
to tie the knot with Robert.

77
00:11:53,335 --> 00:11:56,780
We don't even know each other so well.

78
00:11:57,680 --> 00:12:00,560
And they are talking about our relationship

79
00:12:00,560 --> 00:12:02,020
and our marriage.

80
00:12:02,902 --> 00:12:04,544
How would that be possible?

81
00:12:06,982 --> 00:12:08,520
I know how you feel, daughter.

82
00:12:09,257 --> 00:12:11,980
But it might not turn
out as badly as you think.

83
00:12:12,685 --> 00:12:13,942
Take your father and me.

84
00:12:14,880 --> 00:12:16,906
Our marriage was also arranged,

85
00:12:18,300 --> 00:12:20,920
but, in the end, I just love him.

86
00:12:22,060 --> 00:12:24,200
But the idea of marraige
is not yet my concern.

87
00:12:24,200 --> 00:12:25,866
Also the idea of moving
out and being a wife.

88
00:12:26,586 --> 00:12:29,299
You know that I want to further my studies.

89
00:12:30,720 --> 00:12:33,820
I want to work in the
government services like Father.

90
00:12:33,866 --> 00:12:35,800
But isn't it too unrealistic?

91
00:12:37,017 --> 00:12:42,910
Women like us have been expected to
take care of households.

92
00:12:43,844 --> 00:12:47,120
There's no room for us there.

93
00:12:48,137 --> 00:12:50,280
So how would my life be afterwards, Mother?

94
00:13:01,226 --> 00:13:04,270
What if the marriage came true?

95
00:13:05,457 --> 00:13:06,760
Why don't you consider it

96
00:13:07,355 --> 00:13:10,880
to be for your honor and your family?

97
00:13:11,342 --> 00:13:16,541
Whenever you could no
longer endure your marriage life,

98
00:13:17,726 --> 00:13:19,540
you would always have
some paths to choose from.

99
00:13:21,572 --> 00:13:23,360
Mark my words, Eeang Peung.

100
00:13:40,916 --> 00:13:45,120
Are you afraid of me, Eeang Peung?

101
00:13:49,430 --> 00:13:50,270
No, I'm not.

102
00:13:51,190 --> 00:13:54,267
I... I'm just...

103
00:13:56,120 --> 00:13:57,360
Don't be afraid.

104
00:13:59,489 --> 00:14:01,660
If you still distrust me,

105
00:14:02,920 --> 00:14:03,723
it's fine.

106
00:14:04,905 --> 00:14:06,710
I will never to anything to you

107
00:14:06,955 --> 00:14:09,522
until you consent to it.

108
00:14:10,494 --> 00:14:11,360
Don't worry.

109
00:14:18,186 --> 00:14:19,134
Thank you.

110
00:15:40,186 --> 00:15:41,066
Are you awake?

111
00:15:50,281 --> 00:15:52,540
I really can't get rid of
this thought from my head.

112
00:15:56,568 --> 00:15:57,395
It's all right.

113
00:15:59,288 --> 00:16:02,560
Now you have me.

114
00:16:06,426 --> 00:16:07,825
I will never let you

115
00:16:09,677 --> 00:16:11,531
suffer all alone,

116
00:16:16,405 --> 00:16:19,840
at least in this house.

117
00:16:22,410 --> 00:16:24,857
I will cure your sufferings,

118
00:16:26,685 --> 00:16:27,840
easing them off.

119
00:16:37,750 --> 00:16:39,215
I love you so much, Maey.

120
00:16:44,037 --> 00:16:45,392
I live you too, Khun Eeang Peung.

121
00:17:08,255 --> 00:17:09,940
What the hell are you doing?!

122
00:17:13,107 --> 00:17:14,255
Hey! Maey!

123
00:17:15,960 --> 00:17:16,450
Maey!

124
00:17:21,242 --> 00:17:23,480
You, get this harlot out from this house!

125
00:17:24,392 --> 00:17:25,070
Now!

126
00:17:26,030 --> 00:17:26,835
Yes! Ouch!

127
00:17:28,985 --> 00:17:29,515
Maey!

128
00:17:30,642 --> 00:17:31,535
Stop! Stop!

129
00:17:31,840 --> 00:17:35,276
Khun Eeang Peung, please!

130
00:17:35,993 --> 00:17:36,678
Maey!

131
00:18:11,960 --> 00:18:12,926
Jom, come here.

132
00:18:13,372 --> 00:18:14,350
What are you doing, Khun Yai?

133
00:18:14,945 --> 00:18:15,740
Come on.

134
00:18:16,240 --> 00:18:17,810
Trust me.

135
00:18:19,560 --> 00:18:25,385
Wow! Did you prepare all these on your own?

136
00:18:27,130 --> 00:18:27,460
Yes.

137
00:18:34,710 --> 00:18:36,855
I noticed you were nervous about something,

138
00:18:38,845 --> 00:18:42,650
something I can't percieve.

139
00:18:44,285 --> 00:18:47,405
But what I could and should do

140
00:18:48,250 --> 00:18:49,450
as your lover

141
00:18:51,770 --> 00:18:55,880
is... to make you feel more relaxed.

142
00:19:10,005 --> 00:19:10,960
Come on!

143
00:19:12,825 --> 00:19:16,400
Are you sure this is for me,

144
00:19:18,400 --> 00:19:19,140
not yourself?

145
00:19:22,380 --> 00:19:23,120
For us, honestly.

146
00:19:48,480 --> 00:19:50,195
Get rid of negative
thoughts from your mind.

147
00:19:52,190 --> 00:19:53,360
Just at this time.

148
00:20:20,710 --> 00:20:21,960
Your skin...

149
00:20:23,945 --> 00:20:24,930
it's very smooth.

150
00:20:28,585 --> 00:20:32,860
Thanks to your olive oil.

151
00:20:36,960 --> 00:20:38,300
I knew it.

152
00:20:51,680 --> 00:20:52,350
Khun Yai,

153
00:20:53,765 --> 00:20:58,020
what makes you like plumeria?

154
00:21:05,005 --> 00:21:06,910
Well, why are you asking this?

155
00:21:10,900 --> 00:21:15,870
They're quite an unpopular
flower, aren't they?

156
00:21:16,110 --> 00:21:19,190
Because the Thai name means misery,

157
00:21:20,190 --> 00:21:21,798
which sounds quite inauspicious.

158
00:21:32,708 --> 00:21:33,916
So try smelling it.

159
00:21:42,377 --> 00:21:46,468
Its gentle scent makes me feel liberated,

160
00:21:47,740 --> 00:21:52,777
and it's also enchanting.

161
00:21:54,380 --> 00:21:59,580
I think, it smells like you, Jom.

162
00:22:10,480 --> 00:22:19,224
♪ When our eyes meet, it's
like I've known you forever ♪

163
00:22:19,744 --> 00:22:22,504
♪ Been waiting for us to be together ♪

164
00:22:22,784 --> 00:22:31,302
♪ Dear, my dearest, I've
been defeated completely ♪

165
00:22:31,657 --> 00:22:35,460
♪ Even in the afterlife,
I'll be loving you solely ♪

166
00:22:35,460 --> 00:22:38,071
♪ When our eyes meet ♪

167
00:22:38,234 --> 00:22:43,920
♪ It's like I've loved you forever ♪

168
